qas.question: The Ottoman Empire had no choice but to develop their relationship with what country?
Who did the British Empire side with?
The formation of the Triple Entente and the Triple Alliance partly caused what?
By what year were three empires gone?

context: If the British Empire was now going to side with <a2_0>the Russian Empire<a2_0/>, the Ottoman Empire had no choice but to cultivate a relationship with the <a0_0>Austro-Hungarian Empire<a0_0/>, which was supported by <a1_0>the German Empire<a1_0/>. In a few years these alignments became the Triple Entente and the Triple Alliance (already formed in 1882), which were in part a cause of <a3_0>World War I<a3_0/>. By its end in <a4_0>1918<a4_0/> three empires were gone, a fourth was about to fall to revolution, and two more, the British and French, were forced to yield in revolutions started under the aegis of their own ideologies.
